gg_intro2.content: And I'm Trini! Welcome to my garden!

gg_intro3.content: and in the summer, Alaska gets A LOT of sunlight,
so our veggies can get really big.

gg_intro4.content: Help us grow giant vegetables to eat!
Maybe we'll even win prizes at the Alaska State Fair!

gg_menu_unlocked.content: We've got a new vegetable to grow!

gg_soil_watered.content: Awesome! Our soil isn't dry anymore. And our plants are growing!

gg_plant_dies_compost.content: Don't worry, we can use any plants that have died for compost!

gg_soil_it_intro.content: Which of these will help us find out how to fix our soil?

gg_soil_blog_read.content: A blog post called "Garden Help: Problems with Soil"

gg_soil_blog_correct.content: That's right! We can read that informational blog post to learn how to fix dry soil.

gg_cauliflower_intro.content: We're going to take care of them so they can grow really big for the fair!

gg_aphids_arrive1.content: Oh no! Tiny insects called "aphids" are invading our garden.
They will eat parts of our veggies!
What can we read to learn how to remove aphids from our garden?

gg_aphids_ladybugs.content: What tool should we use to remove aphids?

gg_aphids_useladybugs.content: Tap the soil to let out some ladybugs!

gg_aphids_removed.content: Great! Those ladybugs will defend our plant from aphids!

gg_aphids_damage.content: Oh no! The aphids ate some of our plant.
What can we do to stop the aphids?

gg_aphids_it_intro.content: Which of these will help us find out how to remove aphids from our garden?

gg_aphids_blog_read.content: A blog called "Top Ten Biggest Birds"

gg_aphids_book_read.content: A book called "Garden Insects: Removing Aphids"

gg_aphids_it_correct.content: That's right! We can read that information book to learn how to remove aphids.

gg_aphids_incorrect1.content: Hmm, that seed packet won't help us. It's about growing broccoli.
We need to find out about removing aphids.

gg_aphids_incorrect2.content: Hmm, that blog won't help us. It's about the biggest birds.
We need to find out about removing aphids.

gg_it_aphids_explain.content: Cool! This book can help us learn how to remove aphids from the garden!

gg_aphids_it_read.content: Aphids are insects that eat plants. Farmers add ladybugs to their garden. The ladybugs eat the aphids so the plants can grow.

gg_squash_intro.content: We're going to take care of them so they can grow really big for the fair!

gg_hares_arrive1.content: Yikes! A hare! It's hungry for our veggies!
What can we read to learn how to remove hares from the garden?

gg_hares_clover.content: What tool should we use to keep hares away from our veggies?

gg_hares_plantclover.content: Tap the grass to plant clover.

gg_hares_planted.content: Nice! That clover will keep hares out of our garden!

gg_hares_arrive2.content: Oh no! The hare ate some of our plant. What can we do to stop them?

gg_hares_it_intro.content: Which of these will help us find out how to keep hares away from our garden?

gg_hares_seeds_read.content: A seed packet called "Clover Seeds: Help Keep Hares Away"

gg_hares_seeds_correct.content: That's right! We can read that seed packet to learn how to plant clover to help with our hares.

gg_hares_blog_incorrect.content: Hmm, that informational blog post won't help us. It's about growing tomatoes.
We need to find out about getting rid of hares.

gg_hares_book_incorrect.content: Hmm, that book won't help us. It's  a fictional story. That means it's make believe!
We need to find out about getting rid of hares.

gg_it_hares_explain.content: Nice! This seed packet can help us learn how to keep hares away.

gg_hares_it_read.content: Clover can be planted near gardens to keep away animals like hares. Hares eat the clover and leave the garden alone.

gg_radish_intro.content: We're going to take care of them so they can grow really big for the fair!

gg_weeds_damage.content: Oh no! The weeds hurt our plants.

gg_weeds_incorrect1.content: Hmm, that seed packet won't help us.

gg_weeds_incorrect2.content: Hmm, that book won't help us.
We need to find out about getting rid of weeds.

gg_weeds_it_read.content: Weeds are plants that can stop other plants from growing. Gardeners use a tool called a "trowel" to take weeds out of their gardens.

gg_snail_removed.content: Yeah! That trap will catch the snail so we can remove it form the garden!

gg_snail_damage.content: Oh no! The snail ate some of our plant.

gg_snail_incorrect2.content: Hmm, that seed packet won't help us.

gg_it_snail_explain.content: Awesome! This book can help us learn how to keep snails out!

gg_snail_it_read.content: Snails eat vegetable greens. Gardeners use traps to keep snails away from the greens.
